r-killing-row-india-asks-canada-to-withdraw-41-diplomats-by-oct-10-123100300176_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Findia-news%2Fnijjar-killing-row-india-asks-canada-to-withdraw-41-diplomats-by-oct-10-123100300176_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Which%20Way%20Is%20The%20Afghan%20Way%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia's%20Afghanistan%20conundrum%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20seemingly%20contradictory%20situation%20regarding%20Afghanistan%20last%20week.%20While%20the%20Afghan%20embassy%20in%20New%20Delhi%20put%20out%20a%20message%20on%20social%20media%20saying%20they%20were%20shutting%20down%20due%20to%20lack%20of%20cooperation%20from%20the%20Indian%20government%2C%20India's%20representative%20was%20part%20of%20the%20Kazan%20Declaration%20at%20the%20fifth%20meeting%20of%20the%20Moscow%20Format%20Consultations%20where%20nine%20countries%20and%20four%20guests%20of%20honour%20engaged%20with%20the%20Taliban%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Afghan%20embassy%20in%20India%20has%20been%20at%20sea%20since%20the%20Taliban%20takeover%20in%202021.%20The%20diplomats%20and%20staff%20engaged%20by%20the%20former%20Ashraf%20Ghani%20government%20were%20lost%20about%20their%20status%20with%20a%20new%20Taliban%20dispensation%20in%20Kabul%2C%20which%20had%20no%20recognition%20from%20any%20country%20including%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20became%20clear%20in%20less%20than%20a%20year%20after%20the%20Taliban%20takeover%20that%20India%20would%20take%20a%20different%20approach%20towards%20the%20regime%20this%20time%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20New%20Delhi's%20stand%20on%20Taliban's%20earlier%20regime%20in%201996-2001.%20After%20an%20overnight%20operation%20to%20remove%20all%20its%20personnel%20from%20Kabul%20in%20August%202021%2C%20India%20said%20in%20June%202022%20that%20a%20%26quot%3Btechnical%20team%26quot%3B%20would%20be%20based%20in%20Kabul%2C%20in%20what%20was%20seen%20as%20the%20reopening%20of%20the%20embassy%20in%20the%20Afghan%20capital.%20The%20move%20came%20a%20week%20after%20India's%20senior%20diplomat%20dealing%20with%20the%20region%20(Pakistan%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Iran)%20JP%20Singh%20travelled%20to%20Kabul%20and%20met%20with%20acting%20Foreign%20Minister%20Amir%20Khan%20Mottaqi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%20and%20the%20Moscow%20Format%20Consultation%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20Feeling%20left%20out%20of%20the%20loop%20as%20the%20US%20troops%20suddenly%20withdrew%20from%20Afghanistan%20in%20a%20chaotic%20and%20hurried%20manner%2C%20India%20had%20to%20rely%20largely%20on%20Russia%20to%20avoid%20being%20blackballed%20in%20its%20own%20region.%20The%20Russian%20National%20Security%20Advisor%2C%20Nikolai%20Patrushev%2C%20travelled%20to%20India%20twice%20within%20a%20span%20of%20a%20few%20months%20to%20engage%20with%20Indian%20National%20Security%20Adviser%20Ajit%20Doval.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20continued%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20Moscow%20Format%20Consultations%20on%20Afghanistan%20that%20started%20in%202017%20as%20a%20six-party%20discussion%20with%20special%20representatives%20of%20Russia%2C%20Afghanistan%2C%20India%2C%20Iran%2C%20China%20and%20Pakistan.%20However%2C%20since%20the%20Taliban%20takeover%20in%202021%2C%20the%20meeting%20last%20week%20in%20the%20Russian%20city%20of%20Kazan%20was%20the%20first%20time%20that%20a%20Taliban%20representative%20-%20Foreign%20Minister%20Mottaqi%20-%20joined%20the%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Kazan%20Declaration%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20The%20Kazan%20Declaration%20spoke%20of%20the%20security%20situation%2C%20%26quot%3Bappreciated%20the%20current%20Afghan%20authorities%20for%20their%20serious%20fight%20against%20ISIS%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bcalled%20on%20the%20current%20Afghan%20authorities%20to%20take%20effective%20measures%20to%20dismantle%2C%20eliminate%20and%20prevent%20placement%20of%20all%20sorts%20of%20terrorist%20groups%20based%20in%20Afghanistan.%26quot%3B%20It%20also%20mentioned%20the%20reduction%20in%20poppy%20cultivation%20and%20the%20need%20for%20cooperation%20to%20fight%20against%20the%20threats%20of%20terrorism%20and%20drug-trafficking%20emanating%20from%20the%20Afghan%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20%26quot%3Bregretfully%20stated%20that%20there%20had%20been%20no%20progress%20in%20forming%20a%20truly%20inclusive%20government%20in%20Afghanistan%2C%20reflecting%20the%20interests%20of%20all%20ethno-political%20groups%20of%20the%20country%26quot%3B.%20The%20Russian%20Presidential%20envoy%20to%20Afghanistan%2C%20Zamir%20Kabulov%2C%20told%20the%20media%20-%20as%20reported%20by%20Middle%20East%20Monitor%20-%20that%20Moscow%20expected%20additional%20measures%20by%20Kabul%20to%20have%20an%20all-inclusive%20government%20as%20it%20could%20form%20the%20basis%20for%20official%20recognition%20of%20the%20new%20Afghan%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20voice%20for%20women%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20Even%20though%20countries%20are%20coming%20forward%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Taliban%2C%20there%20is%2C%20so%20far%2C%20little%20pressure%20on%20the%20Taliban%20to%20be%20fair%20to%20the%20women%20of%20their%20society.%20The%20Kazan%20declaration%20expressed%20concern%20about%20the%20restrictions%20on%20women's%20employment%20and%20education.%20The%20declaration%20urged%20the%20Taliban%20%26quot%3Bto%20promote%20the%20modern%20education%20in%20the%20schools%20conforming%20to%20international%20standards%26quot%3B.%20This%2C%20when%20the%20Taliban%20has%20denied%20women%20even%20basic%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20August%2C%20the%20Taliban%20banned%20all%20women%20from%20entering%20the%20Band-e-Amir%20national%20park%20in%20Bamiyan%20as%20they%20said%20women%20were%20not%20adhering%20to%20the%20headscarf%20(hijab)%20rule.%20Women%20were%20banned%20from%20working%20for%20the%20government%20and%20later%2C%20for%20domestic%20and%20foreign%20NGOs.%20Girls%20above%20sixth%20grade%20have%20not%20been%20allowed%20school%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20%26quot%3BAppalling%26quot%3B%20Choices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20When%20the%20Taliban%20barred%20women%20from%20engaging%20with%20NGOs%20and%20the%20UN%2C%20a%20statement%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%20had%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bthrough%20this%20ban%2C%20the%20Taliban%20de%20facto%20authorities%20seek%20to%20force%20the%20United%20Nations%20into%20having%20to%20make%20an%20appalling%20choice%20between%20staying%20and%20delivering%20in%20support%20of%20the%20Afghan%20people%20and%20standing%20by%20the%20norms%20and%20principles%20we%20are%20duty-bound%20to%20uphold%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20similar%20%26quot%3Bappalling%20choice%26quot%3B%20is%20confronting%20many%20other%20countries%20on%20their%20engagement%20with%20the%20Taliban%20regime.%20Not%20engaging%20them%20would%20mean%20that%20the%20meagre%20humanitarian%20aid%20being%20supplied%20to%20the%20people%20of%20Afghanistan%20will%20stop%2C%20but%20continuing%20to%20engage%20with%20the%20Taliban%20is%20giving%20them%20some%20sort%20of%20legitimacy%20without%20recognition%2C%20which%20it%20continues%20to%20leverage%20to%20its%20advantage.%20What%20else%20explains%20the%20increasing%20suppression%20of%20women%20and%20the%20continuing%20an%20ad%20hoc%20regime%20without%20fair%20ethnopolitical%20representation%2C%20which%20has%20been%20emphasised%20since%202021%20by%20global%20players%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAfghanistan%20Embassy%20Shutdown%20in%20New%20Delhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20Amidst%20this%20quandary%2C%20as%20the%20Embassy%20of%20Afghanistan%20shut%20down%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20their%20charges%20against%20the%20host%20Indian%20government%20were%20scathing%20and%20saddening%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20They%20accused%20the%20Indian%20government%20of%20lack%20of%20support%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20host%20government%20had%20even%20failed%20to%20renew%20visas%20of%20diplomats.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndian%20government%20sources%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20had%20initially%20said%20while%20they%20were%20looking%20at%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Afghan%20Embassy%20message%20on%20social%20media%2C%20there%20had%20been%20a%20steady%20departure%20of%20diplomats%20to%20third%20countries%2C%20reportedly%20after%20they%20were%20granted%20asylum.%20Reports%20of%20infighting%20amongst%20Embassy%20personnel%20were%20also%20cited.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWho%20are%20the%20real%20Afghans%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%20The%20developments%20leave%20us%20with%20the%20question%20-%20who%20does%20the%20world%20perceive%20as%20the%20real%20Afghan%20right%20now%3F%20Even%20as%20geopolitical%20pragmatism%20drives%20engagement%20with%20the%20Taliban%20-%20which%20is%20still%20not%20recognised%20-%20personnel%20employed%20by%20the%20ousted%20government%20are%20pariah%20now.%20Though%20food%20and%20medicine%20are%20being%20sent%20in%20humanitarian%20aid%2C%20no%20forceful%20voice%20has%20been%20able%20to%20read%20the%20riot%20act%20to%20the%20Taliban%20over%20the%20continued%20suppression%20of%20Afghan%20women.%20It%20is%20between%20these%20paradoxes%20that%20the%20ordinary%20Afghan%20and%20perhaps%20the%20real%20Afghan%20continues%20to%20suffer.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3E(Maha%20Siddiqui%20is%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20extensively%20reported%20on%20public%20policy%20and%20global%20affairs.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696305360000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-01%2Fsihfbdlo_taliban-afp_625x300_15_January_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhich-way-is-the-afghan-way-4444331%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20had%20to%20deal%20with%20a%20seemingly%20contradictory%20situation%20regarding%20Afghanistan%20last%20week.%20While%20the%20Afghan%20em