20debris%20field%20earth%20orbit%20esa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F59e8f591ddd0631d008b5a6b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22953%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20space%20junk.%20Satellites%20and%20debris%20are%20not%20to%20scale.%3Cp%3EESA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20FCC%20announced%20a%20settlement%20with%20the%20Dish%20Network%20over%20one%20of%20the%20company's%20retired%20satellites.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20agency%20said%20Dish%20left%20the%20satellite%20at%20the%20wrong%20disposal%20orbit%20at%20the%20end%20of%20its%20mission.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpace%20junk%20has%20become%20a%20growing%20concern%20as%20more%20and%20more%20companies%20send%20objects%20to%20space.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Communications%20Commission%20announced%20Monday%20it%20has%20fined%20Dish%20Network%20%24150%2C000%20for%20a%20retired%20satellite%20that%20was%20left%20in%20the%20wrong%20place%20in%20space%20as%20concerns%20about%20space%20trash%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FCC%20said%20it%20was%20the%20first%20enforcement%20action%20it's%20ever%20taken%20regarding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fspace-junk-at-critical-density-2015-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espace%20debris%2C%20or%20defunct%20human-made%20objects%20that%20are%20no%20longer%20used%20but%20left%20in%20space.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDish%20reached%20a%20settlement%20with%20the%20FCC%2C%20in%20which%20the%20company%20admitted%20liability%20for%20not%20properly%20disposing%20of%20its%20EchoStar-7%20satellite%20at%20the%20end%20of%20its%20mission.%20EchoStar-7%20was%20initially%20launched%20in%202002.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.fcc.gov%2Fpublic%2Fattachments%2FDOC-397412A1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFCC%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20Dish%20left%20the%20retired%20satellite%20at%20a%20%26quot%3Bdisposal%20orbit%20well%20below%20the%20elevation%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20required.%20Under%20a%20plan%20approved%20by%20the%20FCC%20in%202012%2C%20Dish%20committed%20to%20relocating%20the%20satellite%20at%20the%20end%20of%20its%20mission%20to%20about%20186%20miles%20above%20its%20operational%20geostationary%20arc.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20after%20realizing%20in%202022%20that%20the%20satellite%20was%20low%20on%20propellant%20and%20would%20not%20be%20able%20to%20reach%20that%20altitude%2C%20Dish%20retired%20the%20satellite%20only%20about%2076%20miles%20above%20that%20operational%20arc.%20The%20FCC%20said%20the%20lower%20disposal%20orbit%20could%20pose%20space%20debris%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOrbital%20debris%20in%20space%20jeopardizes%20the%20nation's%20terrestrial%20and%20space-based%20communication%20systems%20by%20increasing%20the%20risk%20of%20damage%20to%20satellite%20communications%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20FCC%20said%20in%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.fcc.gov%2Fpublic%2Fattachments%2FDA-23-888A1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econsent%20decree%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoyaan%20A.%20Egal%2C%20the%20FCC%20Enforcement%20Bureau%20chief%2C%20said%20it%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bbreakthrough%20settlement%26quot%3B%20that%20shows%20the%20agency%20%26quot%3Bhas%20strong%20enforcement%20authority%20and%20capability%20to%20enforce%20its%20vitally%20important%20space%20debris%20rules.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20satellite%20operations%20become%20more%20prevalent%20and%20the%20space%20economy%20accelerates%2C%20we%20must%20be%20certain%20that%20operators%20comply%20with%20their%20commitments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20provided%20to%20Insider%2C%20a%20Dish%20spokesperson%20noted%20that%20the%20FCC's%20Enforcement%20Bureau%20%26quot%3Bmade%20no%20specific%20findings%20that%20EchoStar-7%20poses%20any%20orbital%20debris%20safety%20concerns.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDISH%20has%20a