%3EEngoron%2C%20a%20fan%20of%20puns%20and%20pop%20culture%20references%2C%20routinely%20turns%20to%20humor%20%E2%80%94%20even%20in%20the%20gravest%20of%20hearings%20and%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20certainly%20can%20use%20it%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Trump%20lawyer%20Christopher%20Kise%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%2C%20a%20few%20years%20younger%20than%20Trump%20at%2074%2C%20spent%20his%20early%20years%20in%20Queens%2C%20about%203.8%20miles%20(6%20kilometers)%20east%20of%20the%20former%20president's%20childhood%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron's%20family%20later%20moved%20to%20East%20Williston%20on%20Long%20Island%2C%20where%20he%20ran%20track%20and%20wrote%20for%20the%20student%20newspaper%20at%20The%20Wheatley%20School%2C%20a%20public%20high%20school%20in%20Old%20Westbury%2C%20New%20York%2C%20and%20graduated%20in%201967.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20proud%20alum%2C%20Engoron%20is%20the%20founder%20and%20director%20of%20the%20school's%20alumni%20association%20and%20writes%20an%20online%20newsletter%20with%20news%20about%20fellow%20graduates%20who've%20nicknamed%20him%20the%20%26quot%3BMayor%20of%20Wheatley.%26quot%3B%20He%20even%20posted%20a%20link%20last%20year%20to%20an%20article%20about%20his%20involvement%20in%20the%20Trump%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20one%20newsletter%2C%20he%20posted%20a%20quippy%20call%20to%20action%3A%20%26quot%3BPlease%20send%20me%20your%20autobiography%20before%20someone%20else%20sends%20me%20your%20obituary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%20first%20made%20headlines%20in%201964%2C%20when%20he%20and%20three%20friends%20won%20the%20grand%20prize%20in%20a%20%26quot%3BBanner%20Day%26quot%3B%20contest%20where%20the%20New%20York%20Mets%2C%20then%20just%20two%20years%20into%20their%20existence%2C%20invited%20fans%20to%20parade%20across%20the%20field%20carrying%20banners%20painted%20with%20creative%20messages%20about%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20early%20sign%20of%20Engoron's%20irreverence%2C%20the%20message%20was%20a%20take%20off%20on%20a%20popular%20political%20quote%20from%20the%20era%3A%20%26quot%3BExtremism%20In%20Defense%20Of%20The%20Mets%20Is%20No%20Vice.%26quot%3B%20Engoron%20was%20just%2015%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20attending%20Columbia%20University%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20Engoron%20drove%20a%20taxi%20%E2%80%94%20a%20fact%20he%20revealed%20a%20decade%20ago%20while%20ruling%20against%20then-Mayor%20Michael%20Bloomberg's%20plan%20to%20expand%20yellow%20cab%20service%20outside%20New%20York%20City.%20A%20state%20appeals%20court%20later%20reversed%20that%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron's%20rulings%20are%20rife%20with%20biographical%20information%2C%20part%20full-disclosure%2C%20part%20nostalgia.%20He%20revealed%20in%20one%20decision%20that%20he%20participated%20in%20%26quot%3Bhuge%2C%20sometimes%20boisterous%2C%20Vietnam%20War%20protests.%26quot%3B%20He's%20also%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20free-speech%20absolutist%20and%20said%20he's%20been%20a%20member%20of%20the%20American%20Civil%20Liberties%20Union%20since%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%20got%20his%20law%20degree%20from%20New%20York%20University%20in%201979.%20He's%20worked%20as%20a%20litigator%20and%20was%20a%20law%20clerk%20for%2011%20years%20for%20a%20judge%20in%20the%20same%20court%20where%20he%20now%20sits.%20Engoron%20also%20taught%20piano%20and%20drums%20and%20played%20keyboard%20in%20what%20he%20describes%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bmoderately%20successful%26quot%3B%20bar%20band.%20He's%20been%20married%20three%20times%20and%20has%20four%20children%2C%20according%20to%20his%20Wheatley%20alumni%20page%20biography.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%20joined%20the%20bench%20in%202003%20as%20a%20judge%20on%20the%20New%20York%20City%20Civil%20Court%2C%20which%20handles%20small%20claims%20and%20other%20lesser-stakes%20lawsuits.%20In%202013%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20an%20acting%20justice%20of%20the%20state's%20trial%20court%20and%20ran%20unopposed%20for%20a%20permanent%20post%20in%202015.%20His%20term%20runs%20until%202029%2C%20though%20New%20York%20requires%20judges%20at%20his%20level%20retire%20when%20they%20turn%2076.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20former%20law%20clerk%2C%20Michelle%20Bernstein%20Ravenscroft%2C%20said%20she%20remembered%20Engoron%20being%20%26quot%3Bkind%20and%20approachable%20and%20that%20he%20was%20very%20invested%20in%20making%20sure%20his%20clerks%20had%20a%20good%20learning%20experience%20with%20him.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngoron%20frequently%20peppers%20his%20rulings%20with%20song%20lyrics%2C%20movie%20quotes%20and%20the%20occasional%20New%20York%20City%20history%20lesson.%20He's%20quoted%20Bob%20Dylan%20and%20Shakespeare%20and%20movies%20like%20%26quot%3BCity%20Slickers%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20Marx%20Brothers%20classic%20%26quot%3BDuck%20Soup.%26quot%3B%20He%20signs%20them%20with%20a%20logo%20of%20sorts%2C%20his%20initials%2C%20AE%2C%20drawn%20together%20in%20a%20circle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20Engoron%20turned%20to%20the%20Frank%20Sinatra%20hit%20%26quot%3BLove%20and%20Marriage%26quot%3B%20which%2C%20the%20song%20notes%2C%20%26quot%3Bgo%20together%20like%20a%20horse%20and%20carriage%26quot%3B%20for%20a%20ruling%20restricting%20protests%20on%20horse-drawn%20carriages%20in%20Central%20Park.%20He%20punily%20titled%20a%20subsection%20%26quot%3BBalancing%20of%20the%20Equines%2C%20er%2C%20Equities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202015%20ruling%20on%20the%20custody%20of%20%26quot%3BStevie%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20female%2C%20mixed-breed%2C%20part%20Basenji%20%E2%80%94%20Engoron%20offered%20a%20philosophical%20discussion%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20animals%20%E2%80%94%20or%20lack%20thereof%20%E2%80%94%20while%20reversing%20his%20previous%20ruling%20that%20sought%20to%20do%20what%20was%20in%20the%20pet's%20best%20interest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BConferring%20rights%20on%20animals%20would%20create%20the%20ultimate%20slippery%20slope%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20reasoning%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20dogs%20were%20deemed%20to%20have%20rights%2