%3EA%20Russian%20Su-35%20downed%20by%20Ukrainian%20forces%20in%20the%20Kharkiv%20region%20in%20April%202022.%3Cp%3EPress%20service%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20Armed%20Forces%20General%20Staff%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20way%20to%20avoid%20a%20Ukraine-like%20aerial%20stalemate%20is%20to%20smash%20the%20enemy's%20air%20defenses%2C%20especially%20their%20radars.%20That's%20why%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20is%20developing%20a%20stand-off%20anti-radar%20missile.%20It%20just%20awarded%20a%20%24705%20million%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eglin.af.mil%2FNews%2FArticle-Display%2FArticle%2F3536644%2Fair-force-awards-contract-for-air-to-surface-missile%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Econtract%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Northrop%20Grumman%20for%20the%20Stand-in%20Attack%20Weapon%2C%20or%20SiAW.%20The%20missile%20is%20slated%20to%20be%20deployed%20around%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEssentially%2C%20the%20SiAW%20seems%20to%20be%20the%20latest%20iteration%20of%20anti-radar%20missiles%20that%20have%20been%20around%20since%20the%201960s%20and%20that%20work%20by%20homing%20in%20on%20beams%20from%20radar%20transmitters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20models%2C%20such%20as%20the%20US's%20AGM-45%20Shrike%2C%20were%20only%20moderately%20effective%20in%20the%20Vietnam%20and%20Arab-Israeli%20wars%2C%20where%20the%20missile%20could%20lose%20lock-on%20if%20the%20radar%20was%20turned%20off.%20But%20the%20later%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.af.mil%2FAbout-Us%2FFact-Sheets%2FDisplay%2FArticle%2F104574%2Fagm-88-harm%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAGM-88%20High-%20Speed%20Anti-Radiation%3C%2Fa%3E%20supersonic%20missile%2C%20known%20as%20HARM%2C%20was%20devastating%20in%20Wild%20Weasel%20missions%20against%20Iraqi%20air%20defenses%20during%20Operation%20Desert%20Storm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-quietly-gives-ukraine-anti-radar-missiles-to-fight-russia-2022-8%5C%22%3Egiven%20HARMs%20to%20Ukraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20helped%20the%20Ukrainians%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffighter-jets-unable-to-provide-close-air-support-over-ukraine-2023-3%5C%22%3Emodify%20their%20Russian-designed%20MiG-29%20fighters%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20work%20with%20the%20US-made%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221421%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ukraine%20MiG-29%20AGM-88%20HARM%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b0e5c2ce014759e72949e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221066%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20MiG-29%20with%20an%20AGM-88%20in%20a%20video%20published%20in%20August%202022.%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20air%20force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20currently%20uses%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.navair.navy.mil%2Fproduct%2FAARGM%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAGM-88E%20Advanced%20Anti-radiation%20Guided%20Missile%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20AARGM%2C%20which%20is%20an%20upgraded%20HARM.%20An%20extended%20range%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.northropgrumman.com%2Fnews%2Freleases%2Fnorthrop-grummans-advanced-anti-radiation-guided-missile-extended-range-completes-fourth-successful-missile-live-fire%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAARGM-ER%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20in%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20key%20question%20will%20be%20SiAW's%20range.%20When%20aircraft%20stalk%20anti-aircraft%20weapons%2C%20prudence%20dictates%20they%20stay%20as%20far%20away%20as%20possible.%20While%20the%20HARM%20has%20a%20range%20of%20about%2030%20miles%2C%20depending%20on%20launch%20altitude%2C%20the%20AARGM%20reportedly%20has%20a%20range%20of%2060%20miles%20to%2080%20miles%20and%20the%20AARGM-ER%20of%20more%20than%20100%20miles.%20An%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmissilethreat.csis.org%2Fdefsys%2Fs-400-triumf%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ES-400%3C%2Fa%3E%20anti-aircraft%20missile%20has%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%20roughly%20250%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDetails%20on%20SiAW%20are%20sparse%2C%20though%20Northrop%20Grumman%20describes%20it%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Btail%20controlled%20missile%20for%20increased%20maneuverability%20and%20survivability.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20new%20missile%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20a%20longer%20range%20and%20higher%20speed%20than%20the%20various%20HARM%20models%2C%20which%20have%20a%20speed%20of%20about%20Mach%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20SiAW%20will%20have%20multiple%20seeker%20sensors%20and%20use%20GPS%20in%20addition%20to%20other%20navigational%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.airandspaceforces.com%2Fair-force-northrop-grumman-stand-in-attack-weapon%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAir%20and%20Space%20Forces%20Magazine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20magazine%20also%20noted%20that%20%26quot%3Bdespite%20the%20weapon's%20longer%20range%2C%20the%20term%20'stand-in'%20indicates%20that%20it%20operates%20within%20an%20enemy's%20defended%20airspace%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20suggests%20a%20shorter%20range%20than%20stand-off%20missiles%20such%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-air-force-rapid-dragon-palletized-munitions-catch-chinese-attention-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoint%20Air-to-Surface%20Standoff%20Missile-Extended%20Range%3C%2Fa%3E%20cruise%20missile%2C%20with%20a%20reach%20of%20about%20600%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22526%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Northrop%20Grumman%20Stand-in%20Attack%20Weapon%20missile%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b06c242ecf94db475942f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22395%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20Northrop%20Grumman's%20Stand-in%20Attack%20Weapon.%3Cp%3ENorthrop%20Grumman%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat's%20also%20notable%20is%20SiAW%20is%20meant%20to%20be%20more%20than%20an%20air-defense%20killer.%20The%20Air%20Force%20wants%20a%20munition%20that%20can%20destroy%20enemy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defensenews.com%2Fair%2F2023%2F09%2F26%2Fnorthrop-wins-705-million-contract-for-f-35-air-to-ground-weapon%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emissile%20launchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20including%20those%20of%20anti-aircraft%2C%20cruise%2C%20and%20anti-ship%20missiles%20%E2%80%94%20as%20well%20as%20GPS%20jamming%20stations%20and%20anti-satellite%20installations.%20This%20suggests%20SiAW%20will%20have%20a%20sophisticated%20guidance%20system%20that%20is%20either%20on-board%20or%20data-linked%20to%20other%20sensors%2C%20or%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlso%20significant%20is%20that%20SiAW%20is%20expressly%20designed%20to%20fit%20inside%20the%20F-35's%20internal%20bomb%20bay%20rather%20than%20mounted%20externally.%20This%20will%20limit%20the%20size%20of%20the%20missile.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ultimate%20prize%20here%20is%20countering%20anti-access%2Faerial-denial%2C%20or%20A2%2FAD%2C%20networks.%20If%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20air%20defenses%20%E2%80%94%20or%20perhaps%20those%20of%20Iran%20and%20North%20Korea%20%E2%80%94%20can%20use%20long-range%20air-defense%20radars%20and%20missiles%20effectively%2C%20then%20US%20aircraft%20will%20face%20a%20choice%20between%20staying%20out%20of%20range%2C%20and%20thus%20not%20performing%20their%20missions%2C%20and%20going%20in%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20prohibitive%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20successful%2C%20SiAW%20may%20spare%20American%20commanders%20that%20hard%20choice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20other%20services%20assume%20that%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20air%20superiority%20like%20they've%20had%20for%20the%20last%2030%20years%2C%26quot%3B%20Hecker%2