0in%20your%20book%2C%20is%20that%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20you%20call%20the%20constitutional%20colonial%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20disputing%20that%20because%20of%20the%20enormous%20number%20of%20rights%20it%20confers%2C%20which%20no%20colony%20ever%20had%2C%20no%20empire%20would%20ever%20have%20given.%20But%20you%20have%20another%2C%20I%20think%20odd%20point%20in%20that.%20You%20say%20that%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20is%20colonial%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%20you%20go%20to%20a%20great%20extent%20to%20point%20out%20how%20the%20constitutional%20advisor%20B.%20N.%20Rao%20had%20made%20an%20enormous%20effort%20to%20adapt%20aspects%20of%20western%20constitutions%20which%20we%20were%20taking%20on%2C%20because%20he%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20aspects%20fitted%20India%E2%80%99s%20reality.%20This%20is%20what%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20his%20extensive%20travels%20abroad%2C%20Rao%20realised%20that%20a%20postcolonial%20constitution%20like%20India%E2%80%99s%20could%20not%20simply%20replicate%20a%20western%20stereotype.%20It%20would%20have%20to%20adapt%20such%20models%20to%20suit%20the%20needs%20of%20an%20aspiring%20constitutional%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%20Very%20importantly%20you%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CBold%2C%20original%20thinking%20was%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20to%20decolonise%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%20If%20what%20you%20say%20about%20Rao%20is%20right%2C%20then%20clearly%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20that%20the%20constitution%20that%20emerged%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20263px)%2085vw%2C%20263px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F04135035%2FBN_Rau_1988_stamp_of_India.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22263%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F04135035%2FBN_Rau_1988_stamp_of_India.jpg%20666w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F041