t%20down%20in%20that%20way%2C%20that%20a%20man%20with%20the%20power%20of%20Modi%20is%20hopefully%20encouraged%20to%20fulfil%20the%20procedure.%20Even%20then%20he%20violates%20it%2C%20but%20at%20least%20the%20constitution%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20tell%20procedure%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20just%20feel%20that%20this%20cannot%20happen%20by%20dictation.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20is%20a%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%2C%20which%20cannot%20happen%20because%20the%20constitution%20is%20saying%20in%20some%20painful%20detail%20as%20to%20how%20a%20bill%20is%20to%20be%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20then%20the%20corollary%20to%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20is%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20much%20larger%20case%2C%20because%20I%20think%20that%20we%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20fall%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20seeing%20this%20through%20Modi%20tinted%20glasses.%20I%20think%20that%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20of%20law%2C%20written%20law%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20we%20think%20of%20law%20in%20the%20country%20generally.%20I%20know%20this%20is%20a%20large%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20then%20you%E2%80%99re%20giving%20a%20second%20good%20reason%20as%20to%20why%20the%20constitution%20spelled%20it%20out%20in%20excruciating%20detail.%20The%20framers%20must%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%2C%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20India%2C%20therefore%20we%20must%20spread%20in%20detail%20the%20procedures%20that%20must%20be%20followed.%20Otherwise%2C%20because%20that%20culture%20of%20compliance%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%20people%20will%20deliberately%20short%20circuit%2C%20people%20will%20deliberately%20take%20shortcuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%2C%20and%20this%20may%20sound%20very%20counterintuitive%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20no%20culture%20of%20compliance%20means%20that%20you%20cannot%20impose%20a%20culture%20of%20compliance%20by%20writing%20densely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYou%20can%20certainly%20try.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20mean%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%20did%2C%20that%20was%20very%20much%20the%20effort.%20This%20is%20sort%20of%20maybe%20much%20more%20Gandhian%20in%20this%20way%2C%20but%20I%20would%20say%20that%20we%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20our%20time.%20This%20culture%20of%20compliance%20will%20grow%2C%20the%20sense%20of%20responsibility%20will%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20then%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20of%20the%20constitution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20constitution%20serves%20as%20a%20framework%2C%20but%20as%20to%20how%20a%20bill%20will%20be%20introduced%2C%20some%20conventions%20will%20develop%2C%20so%20let%20conventions%20develop.%20What%20happens%20when%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20conventions%20developed%2C%20is%20that%20you%20spell%20out%20everything%20in%20detail%20and%20then%20nothing%20is%20left%20for%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThere%20is%20a%20view%2C%20that%20in%20fact%20one%20of%20the%20things%20the%20constitution%20did%20was%20actually%20to%20create%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20to%20create%20the%20spirit%20and%20culture%20of%20democracy%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20earlier.%20That%E2%80%99s%20another%20reason%20why%20things%20have%20to%20be%20spelled%20out%2C%20because%20the%20constitution%20was%20actually%20creating%20the%20Indian%20people%20in%20the%20mold.%20It%20wanted%20them%20to%20follow%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20dispute%20this%20view%2C%20while%20I%20agree%20with%20parts%20of%20this%20thesis.%20But%20the%20general%20thesis%2C%20and%20Madhav%20Khosla%20has%20written%20a%20book%20called%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Founding%20Moment%3C%2Fi%3E%20which%20you%20know%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20thesis.%20I%20think%20it%20is%20something%20that%20I%20would%20like%20to%20dispute%2C%20that%20the%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people.%20The%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people%20only%20in%20a%20legal%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%20what%20he%20meant%20is%20the%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people%20in%20a%20democratic%20sense.%20The%20cultural%20compliance%20that%20you%20say%20didn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%20the%20constitution%20sought%20to%20try%20and%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20No.%20I%20think%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20democracy%20in%20India%20starts%20with%20our%20freedom%20movement%2C%20and%20not%20the%20constitution.%20It%20starts%20with%20protesting%20against%20colonial%20rule%20and%20not%20the%20constitution.%20This%20is%20what%20I%20find%20quite%20interesting%2C%20and%20I%20write%20it%20in%20my%20book%20as%20well%2C%20that%20the%20culmination%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20and%20the%20Constitution%20are%20happening%20contemporaneously%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20happening%20in%20two%20different%20worlds.%20The%20freedom%20movement%20is%20all%20about%20non-violence%20and%20satyagraha%3B%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98satyagraha%E2%80%99%20don%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20mention%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%20in%20your%20introduction%20or%20prologue%20you%20explicitly%20say%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20the%20constitution%20at%20all%2C%20and%20yet%20that%20was%20the%20central%20mantra%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement.%20Why%20does%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20make%20the%20constitution%20colonial%2C%20and%20how%20would%20that%20world%20have%20fitted%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20really%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20word%20because%20that%20would%20be%20a%20very%20simplistic%20claim%20to%20make%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20as%20if%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20had%20evaporated%20by%20the%20time%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20came%20into%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%20Shankarrao%20Deo-%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20encapsulated%20with%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99.%20The%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20was%20also%20to%20create%20a%20modern%2C%20free%2C%20independent%20state%20that%20would%20allow%20Indian%20people%20to%20fulfill%20their%20potential%20that%20would%20give%20them%20the%20freedoms%20and%20the%20rights%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%2C%20that%20would%20give%20them%20a%20democratic%20structure%20which%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have.%20All%20of%20that%20was%20fulfilled%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20In%20the%20broader%20sense%2C%20the%20constitution%20had%20one%20thing%20going%20for%20it%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20exactly%20echoing%20what%20the%20freedom%20movement%20did%2C%20the%20spirit%20of%20tolerance%20and%20consensus.%20Yes%2C%20it%20was%20a%20constitution%20that%20came%20about%20through%20great%20consensus%2C%20which%20is%20what%20the%20freedom%20movement%20was%20aspiring%20to%20do.%20But%2C%20the%20text%20of%20the%20constitution%20did%20not%20echo%20that%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20raise%20one%20third%20point%20that%20you%20make%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20be%20honest%20with%20you%2C%20I%20find%20this%20particularly%20bizarre.%20Right%20at%20the%20end%20of%20your%20book%2C%20you%20argue%20that%20the%20treatment%20of%20daily%20wage%20workers%20during%20the%20lockdown%20when%20they%20were%20having%20to%20walk%20hundreds%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20miles%20back%20to%20their%20villages%2C%20is%20somehow%20proof%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20indignity%20of%20being%20made%20to%20squat%20in%20public%20and%20then%20forcibly%20made%20to%20bathe%20in%20disinfectant%2C%20captured%20in%20one%20image%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20colonial%20constitution.%20It%20had%20shown%20its%20true%20colours%20in%20Bareilly%20in%202020%E2%80%9D.%20That%E2%80%99s%20simply%20not%20true.%20What%20happened%20in%20barely%20in%202020%2C%20was%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20disregard%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20it%20was%20defiance%20of%20the%20constitution%20by%20a%20high-handed%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20government%20with%20a%20brute%20majority%20in%20the%20assembly.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20result%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20it%20was%20undermining%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20simplistic%20reading%20Karan%2C%20because%20my%20sense%20is%20that%20the%20state%20towered%20above%20the%20citizens.%20The%20reason%20I%20picked%20that%20example%20is%20because%20it%20was%20very%20graphic%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20all%20seen%20that.%20When%20there%20are%2050%20labourers%20sitting%20on%20their%20haunches%20and%20then%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20officer%20who%E2%80%99s%20spraying%20them%20with%20chemical%20disinfectant%2C%20I%20felt%20ashamed%20as%20an%20Indian%20on%20that%20day%20when%20I%20saw%20that%20photo.%20The%20reason%20as%20to%20why%20we%20are%20in%20this%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20say%20this%20with%20great%20humility%2C%20is%20that%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20enough%2C%20which%20is%20why%20our%20governments%20can%20behave%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377-300x146.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377-1024x498.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-523068%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20infamous%20incident%20from%20March%2030%2C%202020%2C%20when%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20in%20protective%20suits%2C%20used%20a%20hosepipe%20to%20spray%20disinfectant%20on%20migrant%20workers%20before%20allowing%20them%20to%20enter%20the%20town%20of%20Bareilly.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EHad%20this%20matter%20been%20taken%20to%20court%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20struck%20down%20immediately%20and%20the%20judges%20would%20have%20condemned%20the%20government%20for%20doing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOn%20what%20ground%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOn%20the%20grounds%20that%20you%20are%20treating%20people%20as%20if%20they%20are%20slaves%20and%20animals%2C%20breaching%20their%20rights%20of%20freedom%2C%20equality%20and%20liberty.%20All%20of%20those%20would%20have%20stood%20up%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Yes%20but%20this%20matter%20was%20taken%20to%20court.%20The%20last%20I%20know%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20judgment%20on%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20tell%20you%20something.%20That%20is%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20that%20is%20the%20reflection%20of%20the%20judges%20interpreting%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20alacrity%20and%20diligence%20with%20which%20they%20do%20the%20work.%20I%20mean%2C%20you%20can%20have%20a%20great%20constitution%20which%20is%20not%20colonial%2C%20but%20judges%20who%20failed%20to%20act%2C%20who%20deliberately%20kicked%20the%20ball%20down%20the%20road%2C%20who%20come%20up%20with%20perverse%20judgments%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20reflection%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EAbsolutely.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20give%20any%20judge%20who%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%20or%20a%20government%20which%20has%20behaved%20in%20this%20manner%2C%20a%20free%20pass.%20Of%20course%20they%20are%20to%20blame%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20about%20that.%20But%20I%20think%20in%20India%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20this%20very%20convenient%20expression%2C%20that%20%E2%80%98We%20have%20enough%20laws%20which%20are%20good%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20implemented%E2%80%99.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20think%20about%20the%20laws%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20why%20is%20it%20that%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20governments%20and%20judges%20can%20do%20this%20and%20get%20away%20with%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWhich%20law%20would%20have%20permitted%20governments%20to%20bathe%20people%20having%20made%20them%20squat%20on%20the%20road%20with%20disinfectant%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20think%20that%20this%20is%20exactly%20the%20kind%20of%20large%20moral%20question%20which%20a%20constitution%20is%20meant%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20whether%20in%202023%20or%201949%20would%20have%20asked%20themselves%20the%20question%20%E2%80%98How%20do%20I%20cater%20for%20a%20situation%20where%20a%20man%20like%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20will%20make%20people%20squat%20on%20the%20road%20and%20bathe%20them%20with%20disinfectant%3F%E2%80%99%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20constitution%20makers%20didn%E2%80%99t%20think%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20They%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20think%20of%20the%20example%2C%20but%20they%20can%20certainly%20think%20about%20the%20right%20to%20life%20with%20dignity%20being%20completely%20untrammelled.%20I%20think%20this%20is%20something%20that%20that%20can%20be%20thought%20about%20by%20a%20constitutional%20framer%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20what%20Chief%20Justice%20John%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20saying%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20completely%20untrammelled%20means%20the%20constitution%20becomes%20colonial%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20bit%20reductionist.%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that%2C%20but%20the%20constitution%20gives%20the%20state%20huge%20powers%2C%20and%20every%20government%20knows%20that%20and%20that%20is%20what%20they%20use.%20If%20I%20could%20give%20you%20one%20statistic%2C%20because%20I%20found%20this%20quite%20incredible%2C%20some%20of%20my%20colleagues%20at%20Vidhi%20Center%20have%20come%20up%20with%20this%20%E2%80%93%20in%202021%2C%2058%20lakh%20people%20were%20arrested%20in%20India.%20These%20are%20people%20who%20are%20arrested%20by%20following%20the%20procedures%20of%20the%20IPC.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20been%20detained%2C%20that%20is%20without%20a%20legal%20process%2C%20is%2086.6%20lakhs.%20There%20are%2087%20lakh%20people%20who%20have%20been%20detained%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20a%20policeman%20going%2C%20picking%20somebody%20up%20and%20putting%20them%20in%20lock%20up%20for%20a%20day%20or%20two%2C%20because%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20them%20to%20breach%20law%20and%20order%20or%20because%20they%20just%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20the%20look%20of%20their%20face.%20Now%2C%20this%20is%20the%20country%20that%20we%20live%20in.%20It%20will%20not%20happen%2C%20in%20all%20likelihood%2C%20to%20people%20sitting%20in%20Lutyens%20Delhi%2C%20it%20will%20not%20happen%20to%20people%20sitting%20in%20South%20Bombay%2C%20but%20it%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20to%20people%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20that%20fortunate%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20is%20the%20state%20we%20are%20in%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20to%20jump%20from%20that%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20despicable%20situation%20you%20describe.%20By%20no%20means%20would%20I%20justify%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening.%20But%20to%20jump%20from%20that%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20is%20like%20saying%20that%20what%20happened%20in%20America%20in%20the%2050s%20against%20communists%2C%20which%20was%20illegal%20and%20wrong%2C%20means%20that%20the%20American%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3ENo%2C%20I%20think%20that%20we%20have%20to%20look%20at%20who%20is%20responsible%2C%20and%20responsibility%20goes%20all%20the%20way.%20While%20certainly%20for%20something%20of%20this%20nature%2C%20the%20responsibility%20starts%20with%20the%20police%20officer%20who%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%2C%20and%20goes%20right%20up%20to%20a%20framer%20of%20the%20constitution%20who%20is%20unable%20to%20think%20of%20what%20India%20would%20be%20like%20100%20years%20later.%20Because%20as%20I%20was%20saying%2C%20since%20you%20gave%20the%20American%20example%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20John%20Marshall%20of%20the%20United%20States%20had%20a%20very%20good%20quote%2C%20which%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20are%20interpreting%20the%20constitution%2C%20we%20must%20always%20remember%20it%20is%20the%20constitution%20we%20are%20expounding%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20something%20that%20is%20for%20all%20times%20to%20come%2C%20and%20not%20an%20immediate%20expedient%20for%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20put%20it%20like%20this%3A%20your%20argument%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20following%2C%20which%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20most%20people%20agree%20with%20%E2%80%93%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20prevent%20what%20happened%20on%20January%20the%206th%202021%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20constitution%20of%20America%20endorsed%20it%20and%20permitted%20it%20to%20happen.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20failure%20of%20a%20judge%20to%20act%2C%20the%20failure%20of%20a%20police%20officer%20to%20go%20down%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20or%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20go%20to%20the%20top%20to%20act%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20the%20constitution%20is%20to%20blame.%20Those%20individuals%20are%20to%20blame.%20Just%20as%20Trump%20is%20to%20blame%20and%20not%20the%20American%20constitution%2C%20Modi%20or%20the%20policemen%20or%20judges%20are%20to%20blame%2C%20not%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20mean%20blame%20is%20a%20strong%20word%20but%20as%20I%20said%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EResponsible%2C%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EAs%20I%20say%2C%20that%20it%20is%20a%20time%20for%20some%20introspection.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20simply%20say%20and%20I%20think%20it%20makes%20us%20feel%20comfortable%20to%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9COh%20that%20policeman%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%E2%80%9D.%20Yes%2C%20that%20policeman%20isn%E2%80%99t%20doing%20their%20duty%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20have%20to%20ask%20that%20question%20%E2%80%93%20why%20is%20he%20or%20she%20not%20doing%20her%20duty%3F%20I%20think%20that%20goes%20up%20all%20the%20way%2C%20as%20in%20right%20through%20all%20chief%20ministers%20and%20prime%20ministers%2C%20right%20up%20the%20way%20all%20the%20way%20to%20what%20is%20the%20governing%20mechanism%20in%20India.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20certainly%20food%20for%20thought%20to%20see%20as%20to%20can%20the%20constitution%20do%20something%20about%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EDidn%E2%80%99t%20Ambedkar%20have%20something%20to%20say%20about%20this%3F%20No%20matter%20how%20bad%20a%20constitution%2C%20if%20good%20people%20implement%20it%2C%20it%20will%20be%20good.%20He%20said%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%93%20no%20matter%20how%20good%20a%20constitution%2C%20if%20bad%20people%20implement%20it%2C%20it%20will%20be%20bad.%20We%20have%20a%20situation%20in%20India%20where%20progressively%20bad%20to%20worse%20people%20are%20implementing%20it%20at%20all%20levels%2C%20which%20is%20why%20people%20begin%20to%20raise%20questions%20about%20the%20constitution.%20Which%20is%20why%20your%20conclusion%20is%20colonial%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20to%20you%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20colonial%2C%20but%20yes%20bad%20people%20going%20to%20worse%20are%20implementing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20right.%20I%20think%2C%20because%20you%20gave%20the%20American%20example%2C%20the%20American%20constitution%20is%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20will%20be%20bad.%20I%20think%20every%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20unless%20they%20are%20overly%20optimistic%2C%20will%20know%20that%20the%20people%20who%20implement%20the%20constitution%20will%20do%20it%20for%20their%20own%20selfish%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20saying%2