the%20shade%20of%20a%20decades-old%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20tree%20in%20Hatmulla%20village.%20While%20in%20repose%2C%20he%20realised%20that%20this%20tree%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20surviving%20ones%20in%20the%20village%2C%20once%20known%20for%20its%20mighty%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20trees.%20So%20he%20decided%20to%20embark%20on%20a%20mission%20to%20revive%20its%20dwindling%20plantation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELocally%20called%20%3Cem%3Ebou%E2%80%99in%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Eboueen%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Kashmiri%20language%2C%20and%20scientifically%20known%20as%20the%20%3Cem%3EPlatanus%20orientalis%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20tree%20grows%20over%2020%20metres%20in%20height%2C%20while%20its%20girth%20can%20go%20up%20to%2050%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20chinar%20tree%20is%20highly%20revered%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F294161%2Fkashmiri-farmer-haji-mohammad-shafi-sheikh-grows-exotic-pears%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKashmiri%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20serves%20as%20a%20symbol%20of%20the%20region%E2%80%99s%20natural%20heritage.%20The%20tree%20is%20frequently%20portrayed%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20artistic%2C%20poetic%2C%20and%20literary%20works.%20The%20oldest%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20tree%20is%20believed%20to%20be%20over%20700%20years%20old%20and%20is%20in%20Budgam%E2%80%99s%20Chattergam%20village%20with%20a%20girth%20of%20over%2050%20feet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECome%202023%2C%20Khan%20has%20planted%20more%20than%20300%20%3Cem%3Echinars%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Hatmulla%2C%20which%20is%20adjacent%20to%20his%20native%20village%2C%20Nagri%20Malpora.%20Simultaneously%2C%20he%20has%20become%20a%20part%20of%20the%20state%20forest%20department%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20of%20planting%20over%201%2C000%20%3Cem%3Echinars%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20the%20forests%20of%20Kupwara.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20now%20been%2015%20years%20since%20I%20planted%20%3Cem%3Echinars%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Kupwara.%20What%20inspired%20me%20to%20start%20this%20mission%20was%20that%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20part%20of%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F250408%2Fjavid-parsa-restaurant-kashmir-valley-blackout-covid-19-pandemic-food-security-employment-social-platform-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erich%20history%20and%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20was%20fast%20diminishing%20in%20the%20valley%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201075px)%20100vw%2C%201075px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221075%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Khan%20tending%20to%20a%20Chinar%20sapling%20he%20planted.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423.jpg%201075w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423-500x333.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423-768x512.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F1W4A4893_11zon_11zon-1695975423-150x100.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331265%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKhan%20tending%20to%20a%20Chinar%20sapling%20he%20planted%3B%20Picture%20by%20Umar%20Asif.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20his%20journey%20started%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cp%3EWith%20little%20knowledge%20about%20the%20government%20department%20to%20seek%20help%20or%20how%20to%20plant%20these%20trees%2C%20Khan%20started%20experimenting%20with%20its%20twigs.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20started%20looking%20for%20%3Cem%3Echinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F259692%2Fviral-twitter-srinagar-map-artist-maqbool-papier-mache-art-photos%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrees%20in%20my%20district%20%3C%2Fa%3Ewhose%20twigs%20I%20could%20use%20for%20the%20next%20plantations.%20I%20used%20to%20cut%20twigs%20randomly%20and%20plant%20them%20anywhere%20I%20could%20find%20space%20back%20in%20my%20village.%20Despite%20planting%20them%20in%20hundreds%2C%20I%20had%20very%20little%20success%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGradually%2C%20Khan%20learned%20the%20procedure%20after%20consulting%20with%20the%20elders%20and%20experts%20from%20his%20village.%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EChinar%3C%2Fem%3E%20plantation%20is%20a%20skill%20and%20a%20proper%20procedure%20needs%20to%20be%20followed.%20A%20twig%20of%20proper%20length%20is%20needed%20to%20successfully%20achieve%20results%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EExplaining%20the%20process%20in%20detail%2C%20he%20adds%20that%20when%20the%20planted%20twig%20starts%20forming%20roots%2C%20it%20is%20again%20planted%20in%20an%20open%20area.%20This%20entire%20cycle%20takes%20about%20a%20year.%20The%20roots%20grow%20within%20the%20first%20six%20months%20following%20which%2C%20it%20is%20shifted%20to%20the%20new%20plot%20the%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20899px)%20100vw%2C%20899px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FDSC_5229_11zon_11zon-1695975452.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22899%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22One%20of%20the%20few%20remaining%20fully-grown%20chinar%20forests%20in%20Kashmir.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FDSC_5229_11zon_11zon-1695975452.jpg%2089